1
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:35,433
After giving it some thought,

2
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:39,100
I think we'll try doing
a second line of undergarments.

3
00:00:40,767 --> 00:00:43,767
We're discussing it
with Mr. Fujimura from Vanderbilt's.

4
00:00:43,833 --> 00:00:47,367
That means mass production
to be sold in stores?

5
00:00:47,433 --> 00:00:49,000
Prêt-à-porter.

6
00:00:49,867 --> 00:00:51,967
I see you remember "prêt-à-porter".

7
00:00:52,033 --> 00:00:53,167
Yes, I do.

8
00:00:53,867 --> 00:00:57,500
But boss, won't this go against
our custom-made policy?

9
00:00:57,567 --> 00:01:01,633
Our philosophy stays the same.
It doesn't change a thing.

10
00:01:01,700 --> 00:01:05,333
Someone else will be
overseeing the second line.

11
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:08,800
But that person must remain faithful
to the Emotion design.

12
00:01:08,867 --> 00:01:09,867
Exactly.

13
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:15,467
Which aspects of my design will be kept,
and which aspects excluded?

14
00:01:16,900 --> 00:01:19,667
It must be selective,
yet harmonious.

15
00:01:21,067 --> 00:01:23,867
But at an affordable price.
Which means?

16
00:01:24,733 --> 00:01:26,633
Whoever is overseeing the second line

17
00:01:27,667 --> 00:01:30,533
must be more skilled than I am.

18
00:01:33,933 --> 00:01:35,867
What that means is,

19
00:01:36,533 --> 00:01:40,600
while preserving the design qualities
and policies of Emotion,

20
00:01:40,667 --> 00:01:45,767
we must develop a production plan
for a unit price under 10,000 yen.

21
00:01:45,833 --> 00:01:48,233
-What? Me too?
-Of course.

22
00:01:48,300 --> 00:01:51,633
-You do have good taste, Fumika.
-Taste.

23
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:55,067
Well, Mizuki and Fumika,

24
00:01:55,133 --> 00:01:56,733
you'll be competing with each other.

25
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,467
What?

26
00:01:58,533 --> 00:02:03,067
One of you will become
the chief designer of the second line.

27
00:02:04,100 --> 00:02:08,067
Of course, it's also possible
you could both fail.

28
00:02:12,533 --> 00:02:15,500
Mr. Saruhashi, you'll be studying closely
all practical aspects

29
00:02:15,567 --> 00:02:19,167
of the line production process
with Mr. Fujimura.

30
00:02:19,233 --> 00:02:21,367
-You too, Sosuke.
-Right.

31
00:02:21,433 --> 00:02:25,767
If we can't find
a high quality sewing factory,

32
00:02:25,833 --> 00:02:28,067
we won't be able to develop anything.

33
00:02:28,933 --> 00:02:31,633
-This is essential.
-I'm against it.

34
00:02:32,533 --> 00:02:34,400
I think our style is fine the way it is.

35
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:39,333
There's no point in repeating
the same mistake.

36
00:02:40,467 --> 00:02:41,967
The same mistake?

37
00:02:46,133 --> 00:02:49,133
Well, that isn't even an issue

38
00:02:50,333 --> 00:02:53,067
until we can produce something

39
00:02:53,967 --> 00:02:56,733
and establish a procedure
towards a manufacturing line.

40
00:02:59,467 --> 00:03:02,633
But I want to try it.

41
00:03:08,167 --> 00:03:13,600
Come on. You quickly get old
if you aren't competitive.

42
00:03:13,667 --> 00:03:15,267
This is exciting.

43
00:03:15,333 --> 00:03:17,800
The undergarment industry
will take on a new direction

44
00:03:17,867 --> 00:03:20,233
if we can come up
with something different.

45
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:23,133
I've been thinking of doing
something like this for quite some time.

46
00:03:39,933 --> 00:03:41,100
Hey.

47
00:03:42,267 --> 00:03:45,033
Sorry. I--

48
00:03:45,100 --> 00:03:49,500
You need to figure out
if you want to continue working here.

49
00:03:50,100 --> 00:03:52,233
What?
Am I being fired?

50
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:53,867
No, you're not.

51
00:03:53,933 --> 00:03:58,200
I'm only saying you should decide
what to do with your life.

52
00:03:58,267 --> 00:04:02,533
If you stay at Emotion, you won't be able
to develop your own ideas.

53
00:04:03,367 --> 00:04:05,333
You're right, but--

54
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:08,600
Or do you still wish
to continue working here?

55
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:10,600
Think it over.

56
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,033
I will.

57
00:04:18,167 --> 00:04:20,533
Taste? Policy? Sense?

58
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:23,367
I don't understand
any of this fancy stuff!

59
00:04:34,467 --> 00:04:37,600
What's the point of having
all this frill here?

60
00:04:54,567 --> 00:04:55,900
So, we'll be rivals for a while.

61
00:04:56,433 --> 00:04:58,567
I hate being so serious.

62
00:04:58,633 --> 00:05:01,467
I'm just here to make you look good.

63
00:05:04,900 --> 00:05:07,333
Can you do something for me?

64
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:08,400
Sure.

65
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:13,467
Ms. Tokita, I'm designating you
as our delivery person.

66
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:16,467
Really?

67
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:21,500
We've established a mail order system
for distant customers.

68
00:05:21,567 --> 00:05:24,767
We do have customers from Nagoya.

69
00:05:24,833 --> 00:05:27,933
Delivering our product to those customers

70
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,933
is of crucial importance.

71
00:05:35,300 --> 00:05:37,933
I trust you because you're so punctual.

72
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:41,167
Reiko.

73
00:05:42,067 --> 00:05:45,200
Reiko, why did you start working
at Emotion?

74
00:05:45,267 --> 00:05:47,167
What?
Where did that come from?

75
00:05:47,233 --> 00:05:52,000
Well, the boss told me I should decide

76
00:05:52,900 --> 00:05:54,767
whether or not
I want to keep working here.

77
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:58,267
What is she talking about?
You just started.

78
00:05:58,333 --> 00:06:00,633
I'm not sure if it's really for me.

79
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:02,200
I have no sense of style.

80
00:06:03,933 --> 00:06:08,233
Do you think your job
is right for you, Reiko?

81
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:10,733
I just like the president.

82
00:06:12,733 --> 00:06:15,800
I just want to work with her.
That's all.

83
00:06:29,767 --> 00:06:32,400
I know you're busy,
but here's something important.

84
00:06:37,967 --> 00:06:40,967
No! I completely forgot.

85
00:06:41,033 --> 00:06:42,200
What is it?

86
00:06:44,133 --> 00:06:45,633
Do you know this?

87
00:06:46,133 --> 00:06:47,500
Yes.
That, at least, I know.

88
00:06:47,567 --> 00:06:50,400
There will be a party for
the 30th anniversary of the first issue.

89
00:06:50,467 --> 00:06:53,467
-Do I have to go?
-I'm going.

90
00:06:53,533 --> 00:06:54,800
I love those things!

91
00:06:54,867 --> 00:06:58,667
It's the only magazine featuring lingerie.

92
00:06:59,633 --> 00:07:04,467
It's good for us
to regularly show gratitude.

93
00:07:04,533 --> 00:07:06,267
Well, the president's going too.

94
00:07:08,867 --> 00:07:10,300
Reiko, do you want to go?

95
00:07:10,367 --> 00:07:13,700
Sorry, but I'm going
to the opera that night.

96
00:07:15,533 --> 00:07:17,367
-Ms. Tokita.
-Yes?

97
00:07:18,167 --> 00:07:21,100
Can you deliver this
to one of our customers?

98
00:07:21,167 --> 00:07:22,167
Oh.

99
00:07:23,133 --> 00:07:25,233
They asked us to deliver it.

100
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:33,333
I didn't know
your shop made them.

101
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:34,400
Thank you.

102
00:07:35,533 --> 00:07:37,267
And your customer?

103
00:07:37,333 --> 00:07:39,300
Doing final checks on a dress.

104
00:07:39,367 --> 00:07:42,533
She wanted to see it with this bustier.

105
00:07:43,900 --> 00:07:45,800
-Konno.
-Yes?

106
00:07:45,867 --> 00:07:48,700
-Did the bustier arrive?
-I'll bring it now.

107
00:07:48,767 --> 00:07:51,167
-I'll see you later.
-Best of luck.

108
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:55,900
Sorry.
It just came in.

109
00:07:55,967 --> 00:07:57,000
How beautiful.

110
00:07:58,100 --> 00:08:01,133
I think it would go well with this tiara.

111
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:05,633
This one is particularly elegant.
What do you think?

112
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,867
It's really beautiful.

113
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:13,333
Okay.

114
00:08:39,833 --> 00:08:41,433
I'll need a sewing machine.

115
00:08:42,633 --> 00:08:43,900
Wasn't there one here?

116
00:08:52,967 --> 00:08:54,567
How old is this thing?

117
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:01,633
Made in 1978?

118
00:09:02,533 --> 00:09:03,533
How ancient!

119
00:09:06,367 --> 00:09:07,367
Okay.

120
00:09:29,033 --> 00:09:31,600
It's done!

121
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:39,767
Thanks.
So sorry!

122
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,767
I bought it.

123
00:09:46,467 --> 00:09:49,000
So, how does it feel?

124
00:09:50,133 --> 00:09:51,467
Well.

125
00:09:52,667 --> 00:09:53,800
Can I see?

126
00:09:55,367 --> 00:09:56,967
Go ahead.

127
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:05,567
-It feels great on the skin. Really.
-No, no.

128
00:10:06,700 --> 00:10:10,000
It looks like an outfit
the devil would wear.

129
00:10:10,967 --> 00:10:13,033
I'm sorry for making you wear
something so weird.

130
00:10:13,733 --> 00:10:17,367
You definitely look better without it.

131
00:10:18,233 --> 00:10:19,233
Really?

132
00:10:20,633 --> 00:10:21,867
That's shocking.

133
00:10:22,667 --> 00:10:24,033
What is?

134
00:10:25,467 --> 00:10:27,733
I thought it was a compliment.

135
00:10:30,133 --> 00:10:35,033
People say that to me a lot,
that I look better without something on.

136
00:10:36,300 --> 00:10:37,433
What does that mean?

137
00:10:38,067 --> 00:10:40,400
I'm really bad

138
00:10:41,233 --> 00:10:42,233
at modeling clothes.

139
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:46,833
That's not true.
Even now, you look totally hip.

140
00:10:47,367 --> 00:10:49,333
Something's missing.

141
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:51,167
I'm not at the level
of a professional model.

142
00:10:52,767 --> 00:10:55,467
What do you mean?
That's so awful.

143
00:10:56,133 --> 00:10:57,667
What's "style", anyway?

144
00:10:57,733 --> 00:11:01,100
Why take such a vague word so seriously?

145
00:11:02,233 --> 00:11:05,433
I don't think modeling is really for me.

146
00:11:07,067 --> 00:11:08,467
But I can't stop.

147
00:11:09,900 --> 00:11:11,300
It's my way of getting revenge.

148
00:11:12,533 --> 00:11:13,533
What?

149
00:11:16,100 --> 00:11:17,333
I'll get famous

150
00:11:18,567 --> 00:11:19,567
and show everyone

151
00:11:20,467 --> 00:11:21,933
they were wrong.

152
00:11:27,533 --> 00:11:31,833
Sorry.
I got rejected at an audition today.

153
00:11:33,433 --> 00:11:37,333
I'm really dark inside.

154
00:11:38,633 --> 00:11:42,400
You have such an angelic look,
but you also carry darkness inside.

155
00:11:42,467 --> 00:11:43,500
But,

156
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:46,867
I kind of like what's inside.

157
00:11:47,933 --> 00:11:48,933
What?

158
00:11:54,133 --> 00:11:55,567
It's total mud.

159
00:11:57,300 --> 00:11:58,633
Well.

160
00:12:01,867 --> 00:12:04,733
Maybe this actually suits you.

161
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:07,800
Come on, I'm not that devilish.

162
00:12:08,300 --> 00:12:10,033
What?

163
00:13:06,100 --> 00:13:11,133
This week, I need to go to a factory
in Fukui to select some fabric.

164
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:14,067
Would it be all right
if I don't attend the party?

165
00:13:14,133 --> 00:13:17,167
I wanted people to meet you,

166
00:13:17,233 --> 00:13:19,733
since you'll be overseeing
the second line.

167
00:13:20,467 --> 00:13:22,267
But first, we need to
actually produce something.

168
00:13:25,067 --> 00:13:27,567
Well, all right, then.

169
00:13:28,533 --> 00:13:29,633
Thank you.

170
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:33,600
However, I want the number of people
who are attending to remain the same.

171
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:45,033
You.
Come here.

172
00:13:45,100 --> 00:13:47,200
Me? You mean...

173
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:49,633
Really?

174
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:53,333
Go fill your head with everything
that pertains to sense and style

175
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:57,333
until you can't take it anymore
so that you can understand

176
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:59,100
what the word "fancy" really means.

177
00:14:05,133 --> 00:14:08,800
How did you know I was having
a hard time understanding fancy things?

178
00:14:08,867 --> 00:14:13,200
But only if you wear
something appropriate and beautiful.

179
00:14:14,633 --> 00:14:18,967
Think of it as a test
to see if you have what it takes

180
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,400
to do this job.

181
00:14:22,667 --> 00:14:24,233
What?

182
00:14:27,933 --> 00:14:29,533
I'm losing my mind.

183
00:14:30,667 --> 00:14:33,067
That's fine!
It suits you.

184
00:14:33,133 --> 00:14:35,633
Take that one.
You look cute.

185
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:39,833
If you really think so,
then I'll get it.

186
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:42,033
But...

187
00:14:44,233 --> 00:14:46,367
I'll only be wearing it once,

188
00:14:46,433 --> 00:14:48,533
so why should I pay so much?

189
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:50,333
Do you want to rent from my store?

190
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:52,267
We have a good rental selection.

191
00:14:52,333 --> 00:14:54,833
No. I'll buy it.

192
00:14:54,900 --> 00:14:57,133
This is a test

193
00:14:57,200 --> 00:15:00,800
to see if I have what it takes
to work in this industry.

194
00:15:01,633 --> 00:15:04,333
Excuse me.
I'll take this.

195
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:05,800
Thank you very much.

196
00:15:06,733 --> 00:15:09,067
I can make some adjustments
so that it fits you better.

197
00:15:09,933 --> 00:15:14,533
It won't work
unless you take about 10 inches here.

198
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:15,600
It's too loose.

199
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:18,233
Too loose?

200
00:15:22,467 --> 00:15:24,667
What?
One week?

201
00:15:24,733 --> 00:15:26,633
That will be too late.

202
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:30,967
Is there some way
I can have it done by Friday?

203
00:15:31,033 --> 00:15:33,067
Let's see.

204
00:15:35,067 --> 00:15:39,467
The soonest it could be ready is 6:00 p.m.
Would that be all right?

205
00:15:39,533 --> 00:15:42,600
Yes. Thank you so much.
That's very helpful.

206
00:15:46,567 --> 00:15:48,833
I made it in time.

207
00:15:48,900 --> 00:15:51,167
The boss finally completed them.

208
00:15:51,233 --> 00:15:53,233
Aren't they beautiful?

209
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:54,300
Yes.

210
00:15:54,367 --> 00:15:56,700
Please, have them delivered
by tomorrow evening.

211
00:15:56,767 --> 00:15:58,800
-Confirm the orders.
-Right.

212
00:15:58,867 --> 00:16:01,500
Casablanca to Nagoya.
Lily Magnolias to Tokyo.

213
00:16:01,567 --> 00:16:02,767
Yes.

214
00:16:05,633 --> 00:16:08,600
Ms. Nishida. Lily Magnolias.
Leaver lace.

215
00:16:10,533 --> 00:16:13,800
Ms. Kondo. Casablanca.
Beige base.

216
00:16:20,067 --> 00:16:22,700
Ms. Tokita,
you're a good wrapper.

217
00:16:22,767 --> 00:16:24,967
Origami has always come in handy.

218
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:34,800
I'm sending them off.
They'll be delivered tomorrow.

219
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:41,867
No, Miki.

220
00:16:43,633 --> 00:16:44,633
Welcome.

221
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:48,133
Is it that time already?

222
00:16:50,333 --> 00:16:52,067
Your model friend.

223
00:16:52,667 --> 00:16:54,500
She must be suffering.

224
00:16:55,567 --> 00:16:58,667
She has such an innocent look.
And she said it would be her revenge.

225
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:02,133
I was so surprised.

226
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:04,267
Well, anyone would be.

227
00:17:04,333 --> 00:17:06,000
People always hide their true feelings.

228
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:10,800
And if someone is always cheerful
both inside and out,

229
00:17:10,867 --> 00:17:12,133
it's so boring.

230
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:13,400
Like Yuri?

231
00:17:14,100 --> 00:17:15,100
I'm gonna hit you.

232
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:19,400
But what about that party?
I wish I was going too.

233
00:17:19,467 --> 00:17:22,100
I'd wear a dress and very high heels.

234
00:17:22,167 --> 00:17:24,167
That would be awesome.

235
00:17:24,233 --> 00:17:25,733
Heels?

236
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,300
Shoes!

237
00:17:28,867 --> 00:17:30,000
I don't have shoes!

238
00:17:42,567 --> 00:17:44,967
I just can't get used to
seeing you in those.

239
00:17:45,033 --> 00:17:46,933
Is my walk that strange?

240
00:17:48,267 --> 00:17:50,000
I'm sorry for laughing.

241
00:17:50,933 --> 00:17:52,467
I just bought these this morning.

242
00:17:52,533 --> 00:17:56,433
They told me I should wear them all day
and break them in.

243
00:17:57,267 --> 00:17:59,800
Pardon me, but I'm off now.

244
00:17:59,867 --> 00:18:01,900
At what time will you arrive in Fukui?

245
00:18:01,967 --> 00:18:03,767
Past 2:00 p.m.

246
00:18:03,833 --> 00:18:06,067
There's a meeting
at the factory at 3:00 p.m.

247
00:18:06,133 --> 00:18:07,467
Take care.

248
00:18:09,667 --> 00:18:13,533
Best of luck at today's party.
It will be worth it.

249
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:15,500
You'll get a good idea
what this industry is all about.

250
00:18:15,567 --> 00:18:17,533
I'll study it closely.

251
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:20,333
Don't worry,
I bought some shoes.

252
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:23,400
-How cute. See you later.
-Okay.

253
00:18:26,233 --> 00:18:27,967
We need to head out, too.

254
00:18:28,033 --> 00:18:29,167
Of course.

255
00:18:29,233 --> 00:18:31,000
Isn't the party at 7:00 p.m.?

256
00:18:31,067 --> 00:18:33,733
I'm off to a meeting
at a reputable sewing factory.

257
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:36,033
They're making a sample for us.

258
00:18:36,100 --> 00:18:38,667
Wait, that means I won't have enough time.

259
00:18:38,733 --> 00:18:42,400
Hime, can you deliver
this manuscript to the editor?

260
00:18:42,467 --> 00:18:45,400
Here's the proof of the interview
for printing by 5:00 p.m.

261
00:18:45,467 --> 00:18:46,833
You can go home after that.

262
